1. Argocd installation
    # kubectl create namespace argocd
    # kubectl apply -n argocd \
   -f https://raw.githubusercontent.com/argoproj/argo-cd/stable/manifests/install.yaml

2. To start argocd
    # kubectl port-forward svc/argocd-server -n argocd 8082:443

3. To login to argocs
    # kubectl -n argocd get secret argocd-initial-admin-secret \
    -o jsonpath="{.data.password}" | base64 -d

4. Creating argocd.yaml
    # We are adding "update manifest" step which is used to update the github code 
    # like deployment.yaml with the latest image version
    # we are creating argocd.yaml to updated the deployed pod with the new build

5. To create argo cd application
    # kubectl apply -f application.yaml

6. After creating application it creates a cluster in the argoCD which auto deploys deployment and service yaml files

7. use of selfHeal and prune in the application code
    # prune: true	When service gets deleted manually, argocd needs to be deleted automatically. So we use prune
	
    # selfHeal: true 	If user manually changes any code then argocd needs to update the code and synchronizes in git and pod parallely.

8. If we edit deployment.yaml file and push the code to github. ArgoCD auto updates the pods in the cluster

9. If the user manually edits the content of pod in the cluster. ArgoCD prunes the manual changes
    # kubectl edit deployment argocd-deployment